## SECTION 12: MOBILE RESPONSIVENESS GUIDELINES

### **12.1 RESPONSIVE BREAKPOINTS**

```
MOBILE (< 576px):
- Single column layouts
- Full-width elements with padding
- Hamburger menu (hide desktop nav)
- Touch-friendly buttons: min 44px x 44px
- Font sizes: 14-16px (readable without zoom)
- Images: Optimized for retina (2x pixel density)

TABLET (576px - 1024px):
- 2-column layouts where applicable
- Condensed navigation (some dropdown items hidden)
- Hero section: Side-by-side on wider tablets
- Product grid: 2-3 columns
- Form: Full-width with generous padding

DESKTOP (> 1024px):
- Full designs as specified
- 4-column product grids
- Horizontal navigation fully visible
- Hero: Side-by-side layout
- Multi-column layouts

LARGE DESKTOP (> 1400px):
- Max-width containers: 1400px (centered)
- Wider spacing/padding
- No text line length > 80 characters
```

---

### **12.2 MOBILE-SPECIFIC OPTIMIZATIONS**

```
1. TOUCH INTERACTIONS:
   - Minimum button size: 44x44px
   - Spacing between clickable elements: 8px min
   - No hover states (they don't exist on mobile)
   - Tap feedback: Color change or scale-up
   - Long-press: Show tooltip (optional)

2. KEYBOARD:
   - Ensure keyboard navigation works
   - Focus states clearly visible
   - Tab order logical (top to bottom)
   - Input focus: Auto-zoom to 16px to prevent zoom
   - Keyboard shortcuts: Avoid conflicting with device shortcuts

3. IMAGES:
   - Format: WebP for modern browsers, JPEG fallback
   - Lazy loading: Load images on scroll
   - Aspect ratio: Consistent (prevent layout shift)
   - Responsive: srcset for different sizes
   - File size: Optimize for 3G/4G networks

4. FONTS:
   - Min font size: 14px
   - Line height: 1.6 or greater
   - Font: Sans-serif, system fonts preferred (faster load)
   - Weight: 400-600 (avoid ultra-light or ultra-bold)

5. FORMS:
   - Label above input (not beside)
   - Input size: Minimum 44px height
   - Autocomplete: Enabled for common fields
   - Error messaging: Clear, not just color-based
   - Mobile keyboard type: tel for phone, email for email, etc.

6. NAVIGATION:
   - Hamburger menu: Sticky or top-positioned
   - Menu button: 44x44px minimum
   - Overlay menu: Full-height, covers content
   - Links: 44px tall, generous vertical spacing
   - Search bar: Not hidden behind menu (accessible)

7. VIEWPORT:
   - Meta viewport tag: width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0
   - Max-width: 100vw (no horizontal scroll)
   - Avoid fixed widths: Use fluid layouts

8. PERFORMANCE:
   - Page load: <3 seconds (3G speeds)
   - First contentful paint: <1.5 seconds
   - Lighthouse score: Aim for 80+
   - CSS/JS: Minimal blocking (async/defer JS)
```

---

## SECTION 13: VISUAL ASSET REQUIREMENTS

### **13.1 IMAGE SPECIFICATIONS**

```
HERO IMAGE:
- Size: 1920x1080px minimum
- Format: JPG or WebP
- File size: <300KB (optimized)
- Aspect ratio: 16:9
- Subject: Product + lifestyle context
- Alt text: Descriptive, keyword-included

PRODUCT IMAGES:
- Size: 800x1000px (portrait), 1200x800px (landscape)
- Format: JPG or WebP
- File size: <150KB each
- Quantity: 3-4 per product (flat, lifestyle, detail, swatch)
- Consistency: Consistent lighting, white/neutral background for flats
- Alt text: Product name + key features

CATEGORY ICON:
- Size: 120x120px
- Format: SVG (preferred) or PNG
- File size: <20KB
- Transparent background
- Consistent style across all 4-5 category icons

LOGO:
- Size: 200x100px (horizontal), 100x100px (square)
- Format: SVG (preferred) or PNG
- File size: <30KB
- Transparent background
- Readable at small sizes

CERTIFICATION BADGES:
- Size: 180x180px
- Format: PNG or SVG
- File size: <50KB
- Transparent background
- Official logos (OEKO-TEX, GOTS, etc.)

TESTIMONIAL IMAGES (optional):
- Size: 100x100px (profile picture)
- Format: JPG or PNG
- File size: <30KB
- Circular crop
- Good quality/professional

SOCIAL MEDIA THUMBNAILS:
- LinkedIn: 1200x627px
- Instagram: 1080x1080px (square), 1080x1350px (portrait)
- Facebook: 1200x628px
- File format: JPG or PNG

RESPONSIVE IMAGES:
- Provide 2x versions for retina displays
- Use srcset: <img src="image.jpg" srcset="image-2x.jpg 2x">
- Modern format fallback: <picture> with WebP + JPEG
```

---

### **13.2 ICON REQUIREMENTS**

```
ICONS TO CREATE:
- 4-5 category icons (Bed, Bath, Kitchen, Furnishing, Garments)
- 6 trust indicator icons (Heritage, Workforce, Countries, Certs, Quality, etc.)
- Navigation icons (Menu, Search, Close, Arrow, etc.)
- Social media icons (LinkedIn, Instagram, Facebook)
- Certification badges (OEKO-TEX, GOTS)

ICON STYLE:
- Consistent stroke weight: 2px
- Size: 20-24px (for UI elements)
- Color: Market-primary color or white
- Format: SVG (preferred for scalability)
- Fill style: Outline or solid (consistent across set)
```

